data.description: MN350 is building the climate movement in Minnesota! Join us.
data.name: MN350

data.description: We are working together to secure a healthy planet for this and future generations. We are taking climate action now to promote real and lasting social and environmental justice for all people.
data.name: 350 Asheville

data.description: 350 Austin is a local, grassroots organization committed to the goals and strategies of 350.org. We believe that 350 Austin may be uniquely positioned to influence the direction of climate change action. This is because Austin is the capital of Texas, a state with a long history with the fossil fuel industry, including production, processing and distribution of fossil fuels.
data.name: 350 Austin

data.description: We are building a grassroots climate movement, working for deep reductions in carbon pollution the San Francisco Bay Area & beyond. Our vision is: Clean, healthy, and sustainable communities for all, Renewable Energy, Energy Efficiency, Carbon Neutral, An informed and mobilized Bay Area. For all our campaigns and local groups see www.350bayarea.org
data.name: 350 Bay Area

data.description: 350 Bellingham is here to help raise awareness on the impacts of climate change and participate in the global, national and regional 350.org days of action, at the local level. We also support the regional campaign at Power Past Coal, to stop North America's largest proposed coal export terminal along with the divestment campaign at Western Washington University. You can find us on Facebook www.facebook.com/350bellingham and Twitter @350Bellingham.
data.name: 350 Bellingham

data.description: 350Brooklyn is an affiliate of 350.org that works locally to solve the climate crisis through education, organization, and direct action.
data.name: 350Brooklyn

data.description: 350 Bucks County is working to promote a harmonious relationship with our sacred planet. We are committed to reverse climate change through direct action and education.
data.name: 350 Bucks County

data.description: Un grupo para que podamos ponernos de acuerdo y organizar distintas actividades relacionadas con medio ambiente y cambio climático desde la CDMX
data.name: 350 CDMX

data.description: 350 Central Massachusetts, a volunteer led, grassroots environmental justice organization. Our goal is combat the climate crisis in Central Massachusetts and beyond.
data.name: 350 Central Massachusetts

data.description: 350 is building a global grassroots movement to solve the climate crisis. Our chapter formed to tackle the big polluters in the central Virginia region, and to focus on solutions to bring our area the clean, sustainable energy choices we need.
data.name: 350 Central Virginia

data.description: 350 Charlotte is grass-roots oriented and focused on climate change mitigation. We respect and collaborate with all individuals, groups, institutions, and governmental authorities working to address the present climate emergency. We engage actively with local electricity and natural gas providers, banks, and others who jointly hold the potential to join us in realizing a climate stabilized world.
data.name: 350 Charlotte

data.description: We are a volunteer group working to inspire Chicagoans to take on the challenge of climate change. To envision and build toward a future not dominated by fossil fuels and the environmental destruction caused by their mining and use. While connected to a global movement, we take action locally based on issues important to the Chicago area and the mid-west.
data.name: Chicago 350

data.description: 350 Boulder is working locally to help solve the global climate crisis and transition from fossil fuels to a sustainable future. We promote local clean energy, locally-grown organic food, low-GHG planning and transportation, no fracking, and a community that's resilient to the challenges we face from extreme weather and ever rising fossil fuel prices. We meet monthly and are happy to welcome new members to our team to help lead the transition to a safe, healthy future!
data.name: 350 Colorado: Boulder County Node

data.description: 350 Central Colorado is a group of citizens sharing a concern about the emerging regional impact of climate change on our lives in all aspects including health, severe weather events, economy and our future life possibilities.
data.name: 350 Colorado: Central Colorado Node

data.description: 350 Colorado Springs is growing a grassroots movement of committed individuals and businesses that want to promote the health and vitality of Colorado Springs through education and local advocacy. We seek to educate the community about ways to improve energy efficiency and implement renewable energy solutions as well as to advocate for the adoption of a long-term sustainability plan to guide major decisions for our energy future.
data.name: 350 Colorado: Colorado Springs Node

data.description: 350 Metro Denver is organizing passionate climate activists and allies throughout the city of Denver to grow awareness and action on climate issues. All are welcome!
data.name: 350 Colorado: Metro Denver Node

data.description: 350 NoCo volunteers and allies work together in Northern Colorado for bold action to address climate change and transition to a clean energy future!
data.name: 350 Colorado: N. Colorado/Fort Collins Node

data.description: 350 Conejo / San Fernando Valley is proud to be part of the growing global climate movement. In an area with a population of nearly two million, we stand up against fossil fuels and organize for renewable energy.
data.name: 350 Conejo / San Fernando Valley

data.description: 350Corvallis formed in December 2012 to support grass roots climate action at the local and global level. We have regular meetings, put on educational events and participate in various actions. We also work with local and statewide coalitions whenever possible. We welcome people from all walks of life to participate in the group. Click on our group name above to get to our website for the latest information.
data.name: 350 Corvallis

data.description: 350 CT is a group that is organizing for an Emergency transition to a 100% clean renewable energy system, a green mass transit system for all, and a new sustainable economy based on justice and equality.
data.name: 350 CT

data.description: 350Dallas organizes local actions in conjunction with 350.org as well as actions related to locally headquartered companies such as ExxonMobil and actions related to our city, state and US representatives.
data.name: 350Dallas

data.description: We're building a stronger movement for climate and environmental justice in DC. Join our email list to get involved : http://eepurl.com/Ww0r5
data.name: 350 DC

data.description: We are concerned citizens working to build the climate movement in Rhode Island. An affiliate of 350.org, we’re fighting for 100% renewable energy, a clean and sustainable earth, and environmental justice for all. Join us!

data.description: Fossil Free Somerville is a grassroots group of Somerville residents, City workers and retirees who are committed to building a future free from fossil fuels and a strong grassroots climate movement. Building on the successes of the fossil fuel divestment campaign, we pursue strategies to foster a just system based on 100% renewable energy.

data.description: CCAA was formed for the purpose of educating others and actively working towards reversing the anthropogenic climate disruption that threatens the earth. Based in Syracuse, NY, we hope that our efforts spread world wide and that everyone will comprehend the importance of this political battle.
data.name: Climate Change Awareness & Action

data.description: 350 Maine is building a grassroots network across the state to address the crisis of climate change and a world too dependent on dirty fossil fuels. We grow our power collectively to find real and lasting solutions, to end our dependence on fossil fuels, and to build a healthy, just, sustainable life for people and the planet.
data.name: 350 Downeast

data.description: Baltimore350.org serves as a forum for sharing information on environmental issues at the local, state, and federal level. Our goal is to involve Baltimore area citizens in environmental activism by increasing visibility of local grassroots actions and campaigns and by partnering with other organizations. We primarily focus on issues and legislation pertaining to solar and renewable energy and water quality.

data.description: Adirondack TriLakes 350.org is part of a global grassroots climate movement. We're a nonprofit, non-partisan organization based in the Adirondacks TriLakes region.

data.description: 350 Riverside is a countywide volunteer group of grassroots climate activists. Like 350.org, we are building a movement that can hold our leaders accountable to science and justice. We work to keep fossil fuels in the ground; limit emissions; improve air quality; and build a clean, equitable, zero-carbon economy. We believe in the power of climate justice, collaboration, and mass mobilizations to create change, and we are guided by the principles of nonviolence, openness, inclusivity, and service to the movement.
data.name: 350 Riverside

data.description: Join Watertown Faces Climate Change, a local node of 350 Massachusetts! 350 Mass is made up of hundreds of highly engaged volunteers all over the state, supported by staff from Better Future Project. 350 Mass educates the public about global warming and advocates for change through hard-hitting campaigns chosen by volunteers. You can get in touch with the node leaders by emailing Watertown@350ma.org. The group is also affiliated with Watertown Citizens for Peace, Justice and the Environment.

We meet at a time when people could stop in on their lunch break or before their job begins if they work in the afternoon. Please join us!

data.description: Climate Nashville is a groundbreaking group of faith based, social justice, environmental, and business partners that is leading the local charge to move our region beyond fossil fuels toward a 100% renewable energy economy, reduce greenhouse gas emissions and other air pollution, and ensure climate justice. data.name: 350.org Belgium
data.description: We are building a citizen climate activist movement in Belgium. We are part of a creative, non-violent and open movement that aims to engage the people of Belgium and beyond in being part of the solution to catastrophic climate disruption. We organise in a horizontal way and are open to anyone who wants to be part of the solution to the climate crisis. We help with local struggles and also play a part in the European and global movements in addressing the border-less issue that climate change poses. We play our part in creating a more just and equitable world for the future generations that come after us.

data.name: 350 Burundi
data.description: 350 Burundi started in 2009 when we organised the first global day of action on climate change. Individuals, youth and environmental groups became very excited about the action of 350 and joined. In 2010, we organised the Global Work Party when we promoted renewable sources of energy at local level. In 2011, we worked on capacity building and educational activities in secondary schools, we took part in 'Moving Planet Day' at National University, an event that mobilized over 700 participants. The group helped in preparing the Trans-African caravan of hope on climate change, a journey that departed from Bujumbura to Durban, SA for COP 17.Once we get registered, we plan to strengthen partnerships with local actors to be able to implement our projects focused on collecting a data base on the climate status at national level, producing a local documentary film on impacts of climate change and promote larger use of renewable energy. For more: http://campagne350burundi.wordpress.com/

data.description: Fossil Free Düsseldorf ist kurz vor einem großen Erfolg. Seit Jahren kämpft die Gruppe dafür, dass die Stadt ihre letzten RWE-Aktien verkauft. Einen politischen Beschluss gibt es dazu bereits. Nun müssen Tagen folgen. Fossil Free Düsseldorf bleibt am Ball.

data.name: Fossil Free Sachsen

data.name: Fossil Free Frankfurt a. M.
data.description: Fossil Free Frankfurt setzt sich lokal für den Kohleausstieg und Divestment ein.

data.name: Fossil Free Freiburg
data.description: Fossil Free Freiburg hat schon Erfolge feiern können. Im März 2018 hat die Stadt, nach vielen Aktionen und erfolgreicher Öffentlichkeitsarbeit der Gruppe, entschieden nicht mehr in Kohle, Öl und Gas zu investieren. Die Uni will diesen Schritt bislang noch nicht gehen, aber die Gruppe bleibt am Ball. Außerdem startete Fossil Free Freiburg eine Kampagne, die auch vom Bistum Freiburg fordert, Investitionen in Kohle, Öl und Gas zu beenden.

data.name: Fossil Free Göttingen
data.description: Fossil Free Göttingen hat es bereits geschafft die Stadt und ihre Uni davon zu überzeugen, nicht mehr in Kohle, Öl und Gas zu investieren. Mit der Uni hat sich 2018 die erste Stiftungsuni der Divestment-Bewegung angeschlossen. Nun fordert Fossil Free Göttingen dasselbe vom Bistum Hildesheim, zu dem die Stadt Göttingen gehört.

data.name: Fossil Free Hamburg
data.description: Fossil Free Hamburg setzt sich für Divestment, Kohleausstieg und Wärmewende ein.

data.name: Fossil Free Heidelberg
data.description: Fossil Free Heidelberg setzt sich dafür ein, dass die Uni und Stadt nicht mehr in Kohle-, Öl- und Gasunternehmen investieren.

data.name: Fossil Free Hochsauerlandkreis
data.description: Die Gruppe Fossil Free Hochsauerlandkreis kämpft unter dem Motto #RausausRWE für den Verkauf der kommunalen Aktien am Kohleriesen RWE.

data.name: Fossil Free Karlsruhe
data.description: Fossil Free Karlsruhe will den Klimaschutz lokal vorantreiben möchten, weil es ihnen nicht ausreicht, was bisher von Seiten der Stadt Karlsruhe getan wird. Die Ortsgruppe hat die Initiative Faktor2 ins Leben gerufen, um die Nutzung der Sonnenenergie in Karlsruhe voranzutreiben und startet im lokalen Bündnis eine Reihe runder Tische, um mit Entscheider*innen und lokalen Aktueren, ambitionierte Klimaschutzmaßnahmen zu erwirken. Gemeinsam mit Fridays for Future und anderen Gruppen geht die Gruppe regelmäßig zum Protest auf die Straße.

data.name: Fossil Free Kassel
data.description: Fossil Free Kassel hat ihre Uni dazu gebracht das Geldkonto bei der Commerzbank zu kündigen. Denn die Commerzbank investiert überproportional in die Klimakiller Kohle, Öl und Gas. Nun setzt die Gruppe sich dafür ein, dass die Stadt ihre Versorgungsrücklagen frei von den Klimakillern Kohle, Öl und Gas anlegt.

data.name: Fossil Free Kiel

data.name: Fossil Free Leipzig
data.description: Zusammen mit dem BUND Leipzig konnten engagierte Menschen, die Stadt davon überzeugen, nicht mehr in die Klimakiller Kohle, Öl und Gas zu investieren.

data.name: Fossil Free Lüneburg
data.description: Fossil Free Lüneburg kämpft dafür, dass sich die Stadt und die Sparkasse Lüneburg auf eine menschen- und umweltfreundliche Finanzstrategie verpflichten. Sprich: kein Geld mehr für Kohle, Öl und Gas! Wenn ihr dabei sein wollt, meldet euch bei: fossilfree-lg@posteo.de

data.name: Rise for Climate Mainz
data.description: Kurz vor dem globalen Aktionstag Rise for Climate hat sich die Gruppe Rise for Climate Mainz gegründet. In einem breiten Bündnis fordern sie verschiedenste Klimaschutzmaßnahmen und einen schnellen Kohleausstieg. Außerdem wird Rheinland-Pfalz aufgefordert, nicht mehr in Kohle-, Öl und Gasunternehmen zu investieren.

data.name: Fossil Free München
data.description: Unsere selbstgestellte Aufgabe ist es, die Landeshauptstadt München, sowie Münchner Institutionen, Stiftungen, Universitäten und öffentliche wie private Organisationen zu bewegen, ihre Geldanlagen aus dem Bereich der fossilen Brennstoffen abzuziehen. Sie von "Divestment" zu überzeugen und in nachhaltige Geldanlagen zu reinvestieren ist aus unserer Sicht wesentlicher Eckpfeiler für eine wirksame Klimaschutzpolitik.

data.name: Fossil Free Münster
data.description: Fossil Free Münster hat schon große Erfolge gefeiert. 2015 wurde Münster die erste Stadt Deutschlands, die ihre Investitionen in Kohle, Öl, Gas, Atom uvm. stoppte und somit Teil der Divestment Bewegung wurde. Auch die Uni Münster hat einen Teil ihrer Geldanlagen divestiert. Nun bohrt die Gruppe FF Münster wohl ihr bislang dickstes Brett. Seit Jahren setzt sie sich mit kreativen Aktionen, Öffentlichkeitsarbeit und Lobbying dafür ein, dass der Landschaftsverband Westfalen-Lippe mit Sitz in Münster sein millionenschweres RWE-Aktienpaket verkauft.

data.name: Fossil Free Neuss
data.description: Neuss hat ein großes RWE-Aktienpaket. Dürren und Hitzesommer der letzten Jahre machen deutlich, dass Investitionen in den Kohleriesen schon längst der Vergangenheit angehören müssten. Dafür setzt sich Fossil Free Neuss ein.

data.name: Fossil Free Oldenburg
data.description: Die Gruppe Fossil Free Oldenburg hat lange dafür gekämpft, dass die Stadt ihre Investionen in Kohle-, Öl- und Gasunternehmen beendet. Mit Erfolg!

data.name: Divest Sachsen-Anhalt

data.name: Fossil Free Stuttgart
data.description: Fossil Free Stuttgart setzte sich jahrelang dafür ein, dass die Stadt nicht mehr in die Klimakiller Kohle, Öl und Gas investiert. Mit Erfolg. Nun fordern sie vom Bundesland Baden-Württemberg und der Landesbank Baden-Württemberg ebendieses. Ein ambitioniertes Ziel. Packen wirs an.

data.name: Fossil Free Ulm / BUND Ulm
data.description: Worin investieren die Unternehmen und Banken ihr Geld? Oft hat die Investition klimaschädliche Folgen, da sie ein Geschäft mit fossilen Brennstoffen finanziert. Divestment bedeutet klimafreundliche Investionen und Abkehr von Finanzierungen in der Verarbeitung oder Gewinnung von fossilen Brennstoffen. Unter Federführung des BUND arbeitet in Ulm eine engagierte Gruppe  zu diesem Thema - mehr dazu finden Sie hier.

The group aims to learn and support these communities in fighting these projects in order to win and achieve social justice.

data.name: Italian Climate Network
data.description: Italian Climate Network is an association composed by citizens, companies and NGOs engaged in taking on climate  change and promoting a shift in the economic system towards a model characterized by low levels of greenhouse gas emissions. Founded in 2011, Italian Climate Network works with a wide range of actors both from the public and private sector with the aim to raise the awareness about climate change and take action for tackling it. Its activities include but are not limited to scientific as well as general-audience-oriented divulgation on climate topics, participation to the UNFCCC negotiates and the organization of numerous events and campaigns.

data.name: 350 Wellington
data.description:
Wellington, the capital of NZ, is a hot bed of globally-minded public servants, academics, students and savvy tech-heads and artists, and this is reflected in the diverse range group of individuals that make up 350 Wellington. Our primary focus is on encouraging local bodies and institutions in the Wellington region to divest themselves of their fossil fuel assets as well as growing the local grassroots movement.
Contact: Wellington@350.org.nz

data.name: Fossil Free Aoraki
data.description:
Christchurch’s newest climate action group, Fossil Free Aoraki, is starting its first campaign: to switch Fonterra from coal to renewables for drying milk. Fonterra is Aotearoa’s second largest user of coal, so this change will make a massive difference to our climate, but they need our help to kick the habit.
Contact: fossilfreeaoraki@350.org.nz

data.name: Fossil Free New York
data.location: New York City, New York, USA
data.description:
Now, more than ever, New York needs to be a real climate leader. With the White House controlled by fossil fuel interests, and the Trump administration rolling back climate protections, New York must do more to fight climate change for the people. Our vision for a Fossil Free New York includes:

* A fast and just transition to 100% renewable energy
* A ban on all new and planned fossil fuel infrastructure
* Making corporate polluters pay & divesting from fossil fuels

data.name: Divest New York
data.description: New York City's $200 billion pension funds have committed to divest from fossil fuels after 5 years of intense campaigning by climate activists. Now we are working to get the state pension fund, one of the largest in the country, to join New York City and take real climate action.
